<p><i><b>The Bridge on the River Kwai</b></i> is a 1957 <a href="/wiki/World_War_II" title="World War II">World War II</a> <a href="/wiki/Epic_(genre)" title="Epic (genre)">epic</a> film directed by <a href="/wiki/David_Lean" title="David Lean">David Lean</a>, based on the novel <i><a href="/wiki/The_Bridge_over_the_River_Kwai" title="The Bridge over the River Kwai">Le Pont de la RiviÃ¨re Kwai</a></i> (1952) by <a href="/wiki/Pierre_Boulle" title="Pierre Boulle">Pierre Boulle</a>. The film is a work of fiction but borrows the construction of the <a href="/wiki/Burma_Railway" title="Burma Railway">Burma Railway</a> in 1942â43 for its historical setting. It stars <a href="/wiki/William_Holden" title="William Holden">William Holden</a>, <a href="/wiki/Jack_Hawkins" title="Jack Hawkins">Jack Hawkins</a>, <a href="/wiki/Alec_Guinness" title="Alec Guinness">Alec Guinness</a> and <a href="/wiki/Sessue_Hayakawa" title="Sessue Hayakawa">Sessue Hayakawa</a>. The movie was filmed in <a href="/wiki/Dominion_of_Ceylon" title="Dominion of Ceylon">Ceylon</a> (now known as <a href="/wiki/Sri_Lanka" title="Sri Lanka">Sri Lanka</a>). The bridge in the film was located near <a href="/wiki/Kitulgala" title="Kitulgala">Kitulgala</a>.</p>
<p>The film was widely praised, winning seven <a href="/wiki/Academy_Award" title="Academy Award" class="mw-redirect">Academy Awards</a> (including Best Picture) at the <a href="/wiki/30th_Academy_Awards" title="30th Academy Awards">30th Academy Awards</a>; in 1997 this film was deemed "culturally, historically, or aesthetically significant" and selected for preservation in the United States <a href="/wiki/Library_of_Congress" title="Library of Congress">Library of Congress</a> <a href="/wiki/National_Film_Registry" title="National Film Registry">National Film Registry</a>. It is widely considered to be <a href="/wiki/List_of_films_considered_the_best" title="List of films considered the best">one of the greatest films in history</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
